Incinerate		KEY:Incinerate ~ Red Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural										DESC:A great wyrm red dragon can incinerate creatures in its fiery breath.																					SOURCEPAGE:p.98	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(DC %1)|BreathWeaponDC						BENEFIT:A great wyrm red dragon can incinerate creatures in its fiery breath. A creature reduced to fewer than 0 hit points by its breath weapon must make a Fortitude save (DC %1). Failure indicates that the creature is reduced to ash. Creatures destroyed in this way can only be restored to life through true resurrection or similar magic.|BreathWeaponDC
Manipulate Flames	KEY:Manipulate Flames ~ Red Dragon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural										DESC:An old or older red dragon can control any fire spell within %1 feet per age category of the dragon as a standard action.|DragonAgeCatagory*10									SOURCEPAGE:p.98	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(%1 ft.)|DragonAgeCatagory*10					BENEFIT:An old or older red dragon can control any fire spell within %1 feet per age category of the dragon as a standard action. This ability allows it to move any fire effect in the area, as if it were the caster. This ability also allows it to reposition a stationary fire effect, although the new placement must be one allowed by the spell. Finally, for 1 round following the use of this ability, the dragon can control any new fire spell cast within its area of control, as if it were the caster. It can make all decisions allowed to the caster, including canceling the spell if it so desires.|DragonAgeCatagory*10
Melt Stone		KEY:Melt Stone ~ Red Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural										DESC:An ancient or older red dragon can use its breath weapon to melt rock at a range of 100 feet, affecting a %1-foot-radius.|DragonAgeCatagory*5									SOURCEPAGE:p.98														BENEFIT:An ancient or older red dragon can use its breath weapon to melt rock at a range of 100 feet, affecting a %1-foot-radius area per age category. The area becomes lava to a depth of 1 foot. Any creature in contact with the lava takes 20d6 points of fire damage on the first round, 10d6 on the second, and none thereafter as the lava hardens and cools. If used on a wall or ceiling, treat this ability as an avalanche that deals fire damage.|DragonAgeCatagory*5
Smoke Vision	KEY:Smoke Vision ~ Red Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Sense									DESC:A very young red dragon can see perfectly in smoky conditions (such as those created by pyrotechnics).																SOURCEPAGE:p.98

###Block: White Dragon Abilities
# Ability Name	Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type							Define							Description																																					Source Page		Aspects											Description of the Benefits
Blizzard		KEY:Blizzard ~ White Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural										DESC:An ancient white dragon can use its breath weapon to create a blizzard in the area around it as a standard action.																			SOURCEPAGE:p.100													BENEFIT:An ancient white dragon can use its breath weapon to create a blizzard in the area around it as a standard action. This creates heavy snow conditions in a 50-foot radius for 1 minute, centered on the dragon. This snow slows movement (4 squares of movement per square entered) and limits vision as fog does.
Cold Aura		KEY:Cold Aura ~ White Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Aura	DEFINE:ColdAuraRange|5	DEFINE:ColdAuraDamage|1	DESC:An adult white dragon radiates an aura of cold.																														SOURCEPAGE:p.100	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|(%1 ft., %2d6)|ColdAuraRange|ColdAuraDamage	BENEFIT:An adult white dragon radiates an aura of cold. All creatures within %1 feet of the dragon take %2d6 points of cold damage at the beginning of the dragon's turn.|ColdAuraRange|ColdAuraDamage
Freezing Fog	KEY:Freezing Fog ~ White Dragon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.SpellLike											DESC:An old white dragon can use this ability three times per day. It is similar to an acid fog spell but deals cold damage instead of acid damage.														SOURCEPAGE:p.100													BENEFIT:An old white dragon can use this ability three times per day. It is similar to an acid fog spell but deals cold damage instead of acid damage. It also causes a rime of slippery ice to form on any surface the fog touches, creating the effect of a grease spell. The dragon is immune to the grease effect because of its icewalking ability. This ability is the equivalent of a 6th-level spell.
Ice Shape		KEY:Ice Shape ~ White Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural										DESC:A young white dragon can shape ice and snow at will. This ability functions as stone shape, but only targeting ice and snow, not stone. A white dragon's caster level for this effect is %1.|TL						SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Ice Tomb		KEY:Ice Tomb ~ White Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.SpellLike											DESC:A great wyrm can, as a standard action, cause a creature to sink into ice.																									SOURCEPAGE:p.100													BENEFIT:A great wyrm can, as a standard action, cause a creature to sink into ice. This works as imprisonment, but only while the target is touching an icy surface. A white dragon can use this ability once per day (CL %1). Targets entombed by this ability can be freed by casting freedom or by physically freeing the creature from the ice (Hardness 0, 360 hit points).|TL
Icewalking		KEY:Icewalking ~ White Dragon		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:This ability works like the spider climb spell, but the surfaces the dragon climbs must be icy. The dragon can move across icy surfaces without penalty and does not need to make Acrobatics checks to run or charge on ice.	SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Snow Vision		KEY:Snow Vision ~ White Dragon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Sense									DESC:A very young white dragon learns to see perfectly well in snowy conditions. A white dragon does not suffer any penalties to Perception checks while in snow.												SOURCEPAGE:p.100

